Flour Mills of Nigeria Says Its Profit Declined 30% During First Quarter

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-08-10T11:40:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/flour-mills-of-nigeria-says-its-profit-declined-30-during-first-quarter.html
Flour Mills of Nigeria Plc (FLOURMIL) , which
processes grains and sells cement, said its first-quarter profit
fell 30 percent as revenue climbed.  Net income for the three-month period declined to 2.28
billion naira from 3.27 billion naira a year earlier, the
company said in a statement published on the website of the
 Nigerian Stock Exchange  today.  Revenue advanced to 45.9 billion naira from 43.5 billion
naira, Flour Mills said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  